        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 6:12PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 611 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Washburn, or 11 miles northwest of Claude, moving northwest at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Amarillo, Claude, Washburn, and Pantex.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
